
SPA (Single Page Application) Best Practices

Structure
01) Store all page related CSS in one file defined and loaded by HTML head
02) Store Angular app definition is separate app.js
03) Store each Angular controller definition in separate ctrl.js
02) Store all page related 
03) Organize page layout structure using a base template
04) Define separate html footer and header pages and attach to each page
05) Divide every page by labeled HTML div and HTML span for easy replacement
06) Build every replaceable div or span using separate HTML templates

Design
01) assume multiple devices read the same page so auto scale in HTML head
01) tables are easier to read if boundaries between rows and columns are visible
02) tables are easier to read if alternating rows are tinted
03) unique text within a header, footer, h or p should be wrapped in span
04) unlike the keyboard, a mouse can select, deselect, or  hover so use this
    action to alter or update content of web page element tags
05) avoid too hard to read text

